data.description: This home was remodeled in 2021 so welcome home with many upgrades! Neutral modern colors. Newer kitchen cabinets, farmhouse sink and epoxy counter tops as well as stainless appliances. Laminate flooring throughout the home with tile floors in the bathrooms.2 Bedroom 2 Bathroom, nice walk-in closets. Enclosed Glass Florida room with tile floors as well as a Screened-in porch and porch on the front side of home. Nice sized lot on a quiet street towards the end of Brookridge Blvd. Newer Roof (12/2021) and Tie Downs.Brookridge is a 55+ Active Community, but not your typical Manufactured Home Community since you Own your Own Land! Plus, the Homeowners Association cost is kept at a consistently low level and is only $48.00 a month! The Brookridge Community is Gated 24/7 and is brimming with activity boasting a 72-par Championship Golf Course & Pro Shop, Heated Swimming Pool, Tennis/Pickleball and Shuffleboard Courts, Horseshoes, Bocci Ball Court, Club House, Bingo, Crafts, Shows, and many social Groups! There is a real sense of community where you will meet new friends, there is really something for everyone. Brookridge has a great location and is close to shopping, restaurants, and medical facilities. Located close to State Rd. 50/Cortez Blvd. giving you easy access to Orlando. In addition, you are less than a mile from the Suncoast Parkway, your gateway to Tampa, Clearwater, or St. Petersburg leading you to, Airports, Sporting Venues, Cultural Arts, and world-famous Beaches. Our Local Beach, Pine Island is only 13 miles away where you can watch the Sunset and fish at the piers. The Nature Coast is one of the best places in Florida to live. **Pictures showing home vacant are virtually staged**
